===Adjective===
'''hypocoristic'''

# pertaining to a nickname, usually indicating intimacy with the person

====Etymology====
From Ancient Greek ''hupokorizesthai'', "to call by endearing names" (prefix ''[[hypo-]]'', "beneath, secretly", + ''korizesthai'', "to caress", + suffix ''[[-ist]]'', + adjectival suffix ''[[-ic]]'', from Greek suffix ''[[-ikos]]'')